OL,3,C'Britain's wonkiest road' finally set
OL,4,Cto be repaired years after landslip
OL,6,FCouncillor Allison Bucknell,
OL,7,FConservative MP for Lyneham could not
OL,8,Fattend the meeting approving the
OL,9,Fdecision, but in a written letter to
OL,10,Fthe committee, described the landslip
OL,11,Fas a "catastrophic event that has
OL,12,Faffected the lives of so many people".
OL,14,FShe added: "Residents have been
OL,15,Fwaiting long enough."
OL,17,FCouncillor Elizabeth Threlfall,
OL,18,FConservative MP for Brinkworth agreed,
OL,19,Fadding that repair plans sound like a
OL,20,F"very positive move forward".
